  "text": "5-iodoacetamidofluorescein (IAF) labels proteins on all cysteine residues and is compatible with trypsin digestion and MALDI MS identification [CITATION_1] . Label-based mass spectrometry is a powerful tool, but gel-free non-label techniques based only on MS/MS, or nano LC-MS/MS measurements provide the most unbiased approach. An efficient label-free protein identification and quantification method with LC-MS/MS resulted in quantification of 990 proteins within whole cell lysates from non-stressed and nitric oxide stressed S. aureus [CITATION_2] .",
